  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Case against His People"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear the word of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O children of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD has a case",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "against the people of the land:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“There is no truth, no loving devotion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and no knowledge of God in the land!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cursing and lying,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "murder and stealing,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and adultery are rampant;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "one act of bloodshed follows another.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore the land mourns,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all who dwell in it will waste away",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with the beasts of the field and the birds of the air;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even the fish of the sea disappear.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But let no man contend;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let no man offer reproof;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for your people are like those",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who contend with a priest.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2462
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will stumble by day,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the prophet will stumble with you by night;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so I will destroy your mother—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My people are destroyed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for lack of knowledge.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Because you have rejected knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will also reject you as My priests.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Since you have forgotten the law of your God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will also forget your children.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The more they multiplied,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the more they sinned against Me;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they exchanged their Glory",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2463
          },
          {
            "text": "for a thing of disgrace.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They feed on the sins",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2464
          },
          {
            "text": "of My people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and set their hearts on iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And it shall be",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like people, like priest.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will punish both of them for their ways",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and repay them for their deeds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will eat but not be satisfied;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be promiscuous but not multiply.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For they have stopped obeying the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Promiscuity, wine, and new wine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "take away understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My people consult their wooden idols,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their divining rods inform them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For a spirit of prostitution leads them astray",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they have played the harlot against their God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They sacrifice on the mountaintops",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and burn offerings on the hills,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "under oak, poplar, and terebinth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because their shade is pleasant.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And so your daughters turn to prostitution",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your daughters-in-law to adultery.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will not punish your daughters",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they prostitute themselves,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "nor your daughters-in-law",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they commit adultery.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the men themselves go off with prostitutes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and offer sacrifices with shrine prostitutes.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So a people without understanding",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will come to ruin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though you prostitute yourself, O Israel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may Judah avoid such guilt!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not journey to Gilgal,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not go up to Beth-aven,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2465
          },
          {
            "text": "and do not swear on oath,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘As surely as the LORD lives!’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For Israel is as obstinate",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as a stubborn heifer.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Can the LORD now shepherd them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like lambs in an open meadow?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2466
          },
          {
            "text": "is joined to idols;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "leave him alone!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When their liquor is gone,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they turn to prostitution;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their rulers",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2467
          },
          {
            "text": "dearly love disgrace.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The whirlwind has wrapped them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2468
          },
          {
            "text": "in its wings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their sacrifices will bring them shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
